---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Loihi 2 Parity Audit — Catalyst Neuromorphic" description="155 Loihi 2 features mapped to the Catalyst N2 implementation. 152 fully implemented, 3 hardware-only, 0 missing." hasFog={true}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="pt-36 pb-20 px-6 md:px-12" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <a href="/research" class="text-xs text-white/30 hover:text-white/50 transition-colors mb-4 inline-block">&larr; Research</a>
      <h1 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,4.5vw,3.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight">Loihi 2 parity audit</h1>
      <p class="text-white/35 mt-4 max-w-[650px]">155 features identified in Intel's Loihi 2 architecture. Each mapped to the Catalyst N2 implementation and verified against RTL, SDK, and test suite.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RESULTS -->
  <section class="pb-28 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">

      <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-16">
        <div class="card-glass p-6 md:p-8 text-center">
          <div class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-tight text-catalyst-green">152</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-1">Fully implemented</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-white/20 mt-2">Every neuron model, synapse format, learning rule, routing protocol, and observability feature.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-glass p-6 md:p-8 text-center">
          <div class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-tight text-catalyst-blue">3</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-1">Hardware-only</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-white/20 mt-2">Multi-chip serial links. Require physical I/O pins not present on FPGA dev boards.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-glass p-6 md:p-8 text-center">
          <div class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-tight text-white/15">0</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-1">Missing</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-white/20 mt-2">No omissions. No partial implementations.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
      <h2 class="reveal text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Methodology</h2>
      <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-16">
        {[
          { part: '1', title: 'Pipeline ordering', desc: '10 execution stages verified in Loihi 2 order. Synapse accumulation, dendritic processing, neuron update, learning engine, spike generation. The N2 pipeline processes these stages in the same sequence as Loihi 2, ensuring identical computational semantics.' },
          { part: '2', title: 'Feature enumeration', desc: '155 features enumerated from Loihi 2 documentation and publications. Each mapped to an N2 RTL module, SDK function, and test case. Features span neuron models, synapse formats, learning rules, routing protocols, spike encoding, monitoring, and chip-level management.' },
          { part: '3', title: 'Numerical verification', desc: 'CPU simulator: exact integer arithmetic matching Loihi 2 fixed-point semantics. GPU backend: statistically equivalent (floating-point reorder only). FPGA: bit-exact spike output match against CPU reference across all 152 implemented features.' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.05] rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
            <div class="text-[10px] text-catalyst-blue/50 font-mono mb-2">Part {item.part}</div>
            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/70 mb-2">{item.title}</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-white/25 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- FEATURE CATEGORIES -->
      <h2 class="reveal text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Feature categories</h2>
      <p class="reveal text-xs text-white/30 mb-6 max-w-[650px]">The 155 features break down across these categories. Each feature has a corresponding RTL module, SDK API, and automated test.</p>
      <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-16">
        {[
          { category: 'Neuron models', count: 5, desc: 'CUBA LIF, adaptive LIF, Izhikevich, programmable microcode, multi-compartment dendritic processing. Each model verified for voltage dynamics, threshold behaviour, reset, and refractory period.' },
          { category: 'Synapse formats', count: 4, desc: 'CSR sparse, dense matrix, population coding, convolutional. Each format tested with excitatory and inhibitory connections at 1-16 bit precision.' },
          { category: 'Learning rules', count: 3, desc: 'STDP (spike-timing dependent plasticity), three-factor reward-modulated learning, homeostatic threshold adaptation. Weight updates verified against CPU reference at every timestep.' },
          { category: 'Spike encoding', count: 4, desc: 'Binary spikes, 8-bit graded payloads, 16-bit graded payloads, 24-bit graded payloads. Payload integrity verified through the full pipeline.' },
          { category: 'Routing and NoC', count: 2, desc: 'Mesh network-on-chip for cross-core spike delivery. Axonal delays up to 63 timesteps. Multicast fan-out to arbitrary target cores.' },
          { category: 'Monitoring and observability', count: 3, desc: 'Spike probes, voltage probes, current probes. Real-time state readback via PCIe for debugging and analysis.' },
          { category: 'Execution pipeline', count: 10, desc: '10-stage pipeline matching Loihi 2 ordering: pre-spike, synapse, dendritic accumulation, post-synaptic, soma, threshold, spike generation, learning pre, learning post, learning update.' },
          { category: 'Chip management', count: 3, desc: 'Core configuration, network deployment, state reset. The 3 unimplemented features (multi-chip serial links) fall in this category.' },
        ].map(cat => (
          <div class="bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.05] rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/70">{cat.category}</div>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-white/20 bg-white/5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">{cat.count} features</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-xs text-white/25 leading-relaxed">{cat.desc}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- THE 3 UNIMPLEMENTED -->
      <h2 class="reveal text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Unimplemented features</h2>
      <div class="reveal bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.05] rounded-xl p-6 max-w-[700px] mb-16">
        <p class="text-xs text-white/30 leading-relaxed mb-4">Three features require multi-chip serial I/O pins that do not exist on single-FPGA development boards. These are physical interconnect features for scaling beyond a single die.</p>
        <ul class="text-xs text-white/30 leading-relaxed space-y-2" style="list-style:none;padding:0;">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/15">1.</span> Chip-to-chip serial link transmit</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/15">2.</span> Chip-to-chip serial link receive</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-white/15">3.</span> Multi-chip routing coordination</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-xs text-white/30 leading-relaxed mt-4">These are implementable in RTL but not testable on current FPGA platforms. They will be validated when multi-FPGA or ASIC test infrastructure is available.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- REFERENCE -->
      <h2 class="reveal text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Reference</h2>
      <div class="reveal flex gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <a href="/papers/catalyst-n2.pdf" class="btn-pill text-sm" target="_blank">N2 paper (PDF)</a>
        <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18728256" class="btn-pill text-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Zenodo</a>
        <a href="/processors/n2" class="btn-pill text-sm">N2 specifications</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
